title: A Wack Back Rack
itunes:title: A Wack Back Rack
description:
This week's show is all about our evolving thoughts on Horizon: Forbidden West, from art and visual design to combat and gear, the continuation of Zero Dawn's story, and more. Plus: Favorites from the soon-to-be-abolished Wii U and 3DS eShops, an update on the (supposed) Resident Evil 4 remake, Vinny's custom air-cooled wooden console shelf, and more!

Advertise on The Nextlander Podcast at Gumball.fm, or support us on Patreon!

CHAPTERS

(00:00:09) Intro
(00:02:43) What is your current controller storage situation?
(00:09:27) What horrible nightmare could house all this nonsense?
(00:16:35) Horizon Forbidden West [Some Horizon Zero Dawn story spoilers] - PlayStation - February 18
(00:39:13) First Break
(00:39:17) More Horizon Forbidden West [Some Horizon Zero Dawn story spoilers]
(01:17:34) Second Break
(01:17:38) Sifu Updates
(01:19:35) News
(01:19:46) Saying goodbye to the WiiU | 3DS eShop
(01:31:15) Will there ever be a BioShock movie?
(01:34:55) Cyberpunk 2077 gets its Next-Gen update
(01:38:42) Details about Resident Evil 4 Remake surface
(01:42:03) What's next from the creator of Yakuza's new studio?
(01:45:48) Wrapping up and thank you
(01:46:44) Mysterious Benefactor Shoutouts
(01:48:00) Nextlander content updates
(01:49:05) Thanks again and see ya!
